description:
&lt;p&gt;Barts Health is looking for an experienced Band 5 paediatric staff nurse to work within Children’s services at their Royal London site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting and new opportunity has arisen for a full time experienced band 5 nurse to work in the Paediatric surgical departments within the Royal London hospital. The successful candidates will do a rotation of 3 areas which includes Day surgery, theatres and the surgical inpatient ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The unit is part of a versatile and dynamic service, committed to high quality holistic care with an emphasis on working in partnership with the children and their families. The post holder will have excellent communication skills and be adaptable. They will be keen to learn and develop new skills and knowledge through the availability of a variety of training opportunities whilst facilitation the learning needs of others.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Band 5 you will be caring for ill children with the support of senior staff, to allow you to enhance your skills. You will need to be adaptable to the changing pace of clinical care; enjoy learning and participating in team work. Additionally, the post holder will take a role in supporting the nurse in charge in the day to day running of the shift.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Barts Health has a busy and demanding children’s service requiring staff to be flexible in their working. The post holder will be required to work within a challenging clinical environment and undertake shift work which will include nights and weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Nasima Ahmed - Senior Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;nasima.ahmed3@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
